  "body": "Under normal conditions, most nodes will have the current transactions in their pool.\nWhen a connection starts up, all current transactions are sent in both directions.\n\nWe can mimise the amount of transactions sent by tracking which txs where sent by the remote side\nand excluding those from the initial sync. If transactions to send were picked randomly, this would\nensure that most transactions would only be sent once.\n",
